{{Quote|Luke Skywalker&hellip;<br />File: ZC-1905-FT<br />Section: OC-6492<br />Human: 10th Degree<br />Born: Sidereal Era, AS-5670&hellip;<br />Of Master and Mistress Tan Skywalker, on&mdash;|[[Mistress Mnemos]]|<ref name="The Constancia Affair">"[[The Constancia Affair]]"</ref>}}
The term '''Sidereal Era''' was used in relation to a calendar that, as of [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Fusai/Legends|Fusai]], was used for biographical details such as birthdates in the files of the [[BRT supercomputer/Legends|BRT supercomputer]] [[Mistress Mnemos]].<ref name="The Constancia Affair" /><ref name="The Kashyyyk Depths">"[[The Kashyyyk Depths]]"</ref>

==Known dates==
*Birth of [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]]: Sidereal Era AF-5076,<ref name="The Constancia Affair" /> or [[200 BBY/Legends|200 BBY]] in the [[Galactic Standard Calendar]].<ref name="FF">''The Official Star Wars Fact File''; however, [[Star Wars (1977)|Marvel Star Wars]] indicates a birth date of [[100 BBY/Legends|100 BBY]]</ref>
*Birth of [[Gyla Petro]]: Sidereal Era AS-5667.<ref name="The Kashyyyk Depths" />
*Birth of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]: Sidereal Era AS-5670,<ref name="The Constancia Affair" /> or [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]] (16:5:26) in the Galactic Standard Calendar.<ref name="Star Wars Episode III: Revenge of the Sith">{{Film|III}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The term "[[Wikipedia:Orbital period|sidereal period]]" in astronomy is defined as the time that it takes an object to make one full orbit around its sun, relative to the surrounding stars&mdash;in other words, a planet's local "year."

A similar term used in ads on the [[HoloNet News (original website)|HoloNet News]] website is "[[Sentient of the Sidereal]]," which essentially means "Person of the Year." There has never been a connection made in canon between the two items.

